This small app searches the current directory for .java files, tries to find the "package ..." line and move the files to the correct folder.
It will create folders as needed.

Java 1.7 required.

To execute the app you have to:
1. Copy OrganizeJavaSources.jar to the folder where your .java files are;
2. Run java -jar OrganizeJavaSources.jar from a prompt or command line.

